cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper deals with the generation of 3D point-clouds, which is a task related to computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep generative models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of spectral-domain GANs and the transformation between spectral and spatial domains suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper involves unsupervised learning, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of GANs suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
